Context("LimitedNumeric");

$a=list_random(1,4,9,16,25);
$b=random(1,5,1);
$ans=sqrt($a)+$b;

##############################################
TEXT(beginproblem());

BEGIN_PGML

Use a scientific calculator to evaluate this expression:

    [`` \sqrt{[$a]}+[$b]``] = [__________]{$ans}

END_PGML

##############################################

BEGIN_PGML_SOLUTION

When we use a function (like the square root function) in a scientific calculator, we must know where to enter the closing parenthesis.

For this problem, we should enter

    [`` \sqrt{\enspace} ([$a])+[$b] ``]

If we didn't close the parentheses in the wrong place, like

    [`` \sqrt{\enspace} ([$a]+[$b]) ``]

The answer would be wrong.

END_PGML_SOLUTION

